properties.name: Alondra park
properties.description: Posted by Toomanybunnies This Rabbit Dumping Ground is an island in the middle of a park. It is technically unincorporated county of Los Angeles land and has been designated a California Native Plant and Wildlife Preserve. Rabbits Dumped here are eaten by Raccoons, Hawks, and other wildlife and have to compete with Ducks and geese for what little food they can find.

properties.name: Rabbitmatch.org
properties.description: Posted by Toomanybunnies Los Angeles, CA 90064 RabbitMatch.org is a 501c3-pending group of volunteers whose passion is finding abandoned Los Angeles rabbits loving, indoor homes Our wonderful rabbits enjoy human company, are all spayed/neutered, litterbox trained and looking for rabbit-friendly indoor homes. RabbitMatch.org is available for adoption or fostering inquiries, quality rabbit information or just to talk \'rabbits\'. Volunteers and/ or donations are warmly welcomed.

properties.description: Posted by Toomanybunnies 1102 Camino Real, Redondo Beach, CAWilderness Park has been a poplar dumping ground for CAts, Rabbits, Turtles and other unwanted pets for years.
